  "grain": "one row per delivery process EXL runs for an L&A client in this line of business (client \u00d7 named process)",
  "row_count": 181,
  "summary": "Operational inventory of the Individual Life processes EXL delivers for its Life & Annuity clients. Each row is one client process with its standardized process taxonomy (Level 1/2/3), the product lines it covers (Term Life, Whole Life, Universal Life, Indexed Universal Life...), staffing (FTEs, headcount), delivery geography, SLAs (quality, TAT, AHT), volumes, pricing model, automation/digital solutions deployed, and the responsible SME/manager. It lets a rep see exactly what EXL already does for a named L&A client and how that work is staffed, priced, and automated.",
  "use_cases": [
    "Which processes does EXL run for a given L&A client in Individual Life?",
    "What is the headcount / FTE footprint on a client's processes?",
    "Which products or sub-lines does a client's process cover?",
    "Which EXL digital solutions (Exelia, Xtrakto, NerveHub, Customer 360) are deployed at a client?",
    "What delivery locations and countries support a client's processes?",
    "What is the pricing model and SLA profile for a client's processes?"
  ],
